        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1652203081" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11071798307325605079">I thought I was reading Edgar Allan Poe there for a moment. The torture/execution machine in this short story was worthy of Poe&apos;s imagination. What was it&apos;s purpose? To torture or to execute? Either one would be most cruel in it&apos;s application. But in this case it serves the dual purpose. It also had an Orwellian feel to it. Of course Kafka was sandwiched between these two writers so it&apos;s hard to say any influence existed.</span>
  <span id="freeText11071798307325605079" style="display:none">I thought I was reading Edgar Allan Poe there for a moment. The torture/execution machine in this short story was worthy of Poe's imagination. What was it's purpose? To torture or to execute? Either one would be most cruel in it's application. But in this case it serves the dual purpose. It also had an Orwellian feel to it. Of course Kafka was sandwiched between these two writers so it's hard to say any influence existed.</span>
